Class ProfileEditingResource

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.xing.api.Resource
      • com.xing.api.resources.ProfileEditingResource

  • public class ProfileEditingResource
extends Resource
    Represent the 'Profile Editing' resource.

    Provides methods which allow to edit the authorizing user's profile information.

    • Method Detail

      • updateGeneralInformation

        public CallSpec<XingUser,HttpError> updateGeneralInformation()
        Updates the authorizing user's general profile information.

        A successful request will return the user's updated profile.

        Possible optional query parameters:

        Parameter Name Description
        academic_title Updates the users academic title. Must be one of "Dr.", "Prof.", "Prof. Dr.", "Ing.", "Dipl.-Ing.", "Mag." or an empty string. Use empty string to delete value.
        employment_status Updates the users employment status. Must be one of ‘ENTREPRENEUR’, ‘FREELANCER’, ‘EMPLOYEE’, ‘EXECUTIVE’, ‘RECRUITER’, ‘PUBLIC_SERVANT’, ‘UNEMPLOYED’, ‘RETIRED’. See: EmploymentStatus .
        haves List of things you have separated by comma (must not be longer than 2048 characters, each item must not be longer than 200 characters, each item must contain a non-whitespace, not more than 200 items)
        interests List of things you are interested in separated by comma (must not be longer than 2048 characters, each item must not be longer than 200 characters, each item must contain a non-whitespace, not more than 200 items).
        organisation_member List of organizations you are a member of separated by comma (must not be longer than 2048 characters, each item must not be longer than 200 characters, each item must contain a non-whitespace, not more than 200 items).
        wants List of things you want separated by comma (must not be longer than 2048 characters, each item must not be longer than 200 characters, each item must contain a non-whitespace, not more than 200 items).
        Returns:
        A callSpec object ready to execute the request.
        See Also:
        'Update users general information' resource page

      • updateProfilePicture

        public CallSpec<java.lang.Void,HttpError> updateProfilePicture(PictureUpload pictureUpload)
        Updates the authorizing user's profile picture.

        Uploads a new photo and defines it as the users profile picture. Pictures have to be less than 20 MB large. The supported image formats are image/jpeg and image/png.

        It is sent as application/json with the image data Base64 encoded in the body: { "photo": { "file_name": "test.jpg", "mime_type": "image/jpeg", "content": "Base64 encoded image data" } }

        The required PictureUpload Object can be generated by using PictureUpload.pictureUploadJPEG(String, byte[]) or PictureUpload.pictureUploadPNG(String, byte[])

        Returns:
        A callSpec object ready to execute the request.
        See Also:
        'Update users profile picture' resource page

      • updateProfilePicture

        public CallSpec<java.lang.Void,HttpError> updateProfilePicture(RequestBody body)
        Updates the authorizing user's profile picture. This method is for a more advanced use (like setting a multipart body).

        Uploads a new photo and defines it as the users profile picture. Pictures have to be less than 20 MB large. The supported image formats are image/jpeg and image/png.

        Parameters:
        body - Request body to be sent. If null an empty body will be sent.
        Returns:
        A callSpec object ready to execute the request.
        See Also:
        'Update users profile picture' resource page

      • updatePrivateAddress

        public CallSpec<java.lang.Void,HttpError> updatePrivateAddress()
        Updates the authorizing user's private address.

        If a field is not passed, it will not be updated or will be removed. To delete fields you should provide an empty value along with the field.

        Possible optional query/form parameters:

        Parameter Name Description
        city This field can not be unset and may contain up to 49 characters and must have at least 2 characters
        country This field can not be unset and must be an ISO-3166 country code (some countries require a province to be set)
        email This field can be empty or must be a valid email address (foo@example.com)
        fax This field can be empty or must be the country code, area code and number separated by a pipe character (|). Use Phone.
        mobile_phone This field can be empty or must be the country code, area code and number separated by a pipe character (|). Use Phone.
        phone This field can be empty or must be the country code, area code and number separated by a pipe character (|). Use Phone.
        province This field can be empty or may contain up to 79 characters
        street This field can be empty or may contain up to 49 characters
        zip_code This field can be empty or may contain up to 19 characters
        Returns:
        A callSpec object ready to execute the request.
        See Also:
        'Update the users private address' resource page.

      • addSchool

        public CallSpec<School,HttpError> addSchool(java.lang.String name)
        Adds a new school to the authorizing user's education background.

        Possible optional query parameters:

        Parameter Name Description
        begin_date Start date in format YYYY or YYYY-MM. Use SafeCalendar.
        degree The (future) degree. Must be less than 80 characters long.
        end_date End date in format YYYY or YYYY-MM, must be greater than begin_date. Use SafeCalendar.
        notes Additional notes such as specialized subjects. Must be less than 80 characters long.
        subject Describes the field of study. For primary school this field must be supplied. Must be less than 80 characters long.
        Parameters:
        name - Name of the school (must NOT be null).
        Returns:
        A callSpec object ready to execute the request.
        See Also:
        'Create a school' resource page.

      • updateSchool

        public CallSpec<School,HttpError> updateSchool(java.lang.String schoolId)
        Updates the specified school from the authorizing user's educational background.

        Fields that are not provided are considered as not to be updated. Sending an empty field will unset it. The subject field can’t be empty when the specified school is marked as primary school.

        Possible optional query parameters:

        Parameter Name Description
        name Name of the school. Must be less than 80 characters long.
        begin_date Start date in format YYYY or YYYY-MM. Use SafeCalendar.
        degree The (future) degree. Must be less than 80 characters long.
        end_date End date in format YYYY or YYYY-MM, must be greater than begin_date. Use SafeCalendar.
        notes Additional notes such as specialized subjects. Must be less than 80 characters long.
        subject Describes the field of study. For primary school this field must be supplied. Must be less than 80 characters long.
        Parameters:
        schoolId - Id of the School to update. Must NOT be null or empty.
        Returns:
        A callSpec object ready to execute the request.
        See Also:
        'Update a school' resource page.

      • addCompany

        public CallSpec<Company,HttpError> addCompany(java.lang.String name,
                                              java.lang.String title,
                                              FormOfEmployment formOfEmployment)
        Adds a new company to the authorizing user's professional experience.

        Possible optional query/form parameters:

        Parameter Name Description
        begin_date Start date in format YYYY or YYYY-MM. Use SafeCalendar.
        career_level Describes the job level. See CareerLevel for possible values.
        company_size Describes the company size. See CompanySize for possible values.
        description Description of the company. Must not be longer than 512 characters.
        discipline Describes the discipline of the role. See Discipline for possible values.
        end_date End date in format YYYY or YYYY-MM, must be greater than begin_date or null. Use SafeCalendar.
        industries Industries of the company as a comma separated list of ids. See resource web page for more info.
        until_now If true, no end_date should be given. Instead of an end_date, this job will be displayed as ‘to present’ on the profile.
        url URL to the company homepage. Must not be longer than 128 characters.
        Parameters:
        name - Name of the company. Must not be longer than 80 characters.
        title - Job title. Must not be longer than 80 characters.
        formOfEmployment - Form of employment. For possible values see FormOfEmployment.
        Returns:
        A callSpec object ready to execute the request.
        See Also:
        'Add Company' resource page.

      • updateCompany

        public CallSpec<Company,HttpError> updateCompany(java.lang.String companyId)
        Updates the specified company in the authorizing user's professional experience.

        Fields that are not provided are considered as not to be updated. Fields set as null or emtpy will be unset.

        Possible optional query/form parameters:

        Parameter Name Description
        name Name of the company. Must not be longer than 80 characters.
        title The job title. Must not be longer than 80 characters.
        begin_date Start date in format YYYY or YYYY-MM. Use SafeCalendar.
        career_level Describes the job level. See CareerLevel for possible values.
        form_of_employment Describes the form of employment. See FormOfEmployment for possible values.
        company_size Describes the company size. See CompanySize for possible values.
        description Description of the company. Must not be longer than 512 characters.
        discipline Describes the discipline of the role. See Discipline for possible values.
        end_date End date in format YYYY or YYYY-MM, must be greater than begin_date or null. Use SafeCalendar.
        industries Industries of the company as a comma separated list of ids. See resource web page for more info.
        until_now If true, no end_date should be given. Instead of an end_date, this job will be displayed as ‘to present’ on the profile.
        url URL to the company homepage. Must not be longer than 128 characters.
        Parameters:
        companyId - Id of the company to update. Must NOT be null or empty.
        Returns:
        A callSpec object ready to execute the request.
        See Also:
        'Update Company' resource page.

      • updateUsersProfileMessage

        public CallSpec<java.lang.Void,HttpError> updateUsersProfileMessage(java.lang.String userId,
                                                                    java.lang.String message)
        Updates the specified user's profile message.

        Please observe the policies when posting profile messages.

        Possible optional query/form parameters:

        Parameter Name Description
        public Specifies whether the profile message should be visible to everyone (true) or just the user’s direct contacts (false). The default is true. This parameter corresponds to the "only visible to direct contacts" checkbox on a user’s profile page.
        Parameters:
        userId - The user id. Must NOT be null or empty.
        message - Profile message to set. Maximum length is 140 characters. If empty the current profile message will be deleted.
        Returns:
        A callSpec object ready to execute the request.
        See Also:
        'Update users profile massage' respurce page.
